Compare Capt. rv 2, 105 vae aetati (other read- ing vitae) tuae; the same phrase recurs Stich. 1v 2, 14. So also Rud. n 3, 44 vae capiti atque aetati tuae. In Pseud. 1 1, 109 in te nunc omnes spes sunt aetati meae the sense is clearly represented by a simple mihi.
